-- Sierra Leone Sells $1 Million at Foreign-Currency Auction
-- B y   S i l a s   G b a n d i a
-- 2012-03-02T16:07:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/sierra-leone-sells-1-million-at-foreign-currency-auction.html
The Bank of Sierra Leone sold all of
the $1 million it offered at a foreign-currency auction
yesterday, with an average exchange rate of 4,322.60 leones per
dollar, it said in a statement distributed in Freetown, the
capital, today.  The central bank will offer $1 million at its next auction
on March 7, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Silas Gbandia in Freetown via Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  